        HCI/CSCW researcher; empathetic moderator; contemplative flâneur;
        resource-sharing strategist; lifetime learner (plus EV enthusiast
        and unapologetic YouTube binge-watcher). :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}
      </p>
      <p>
        Usually at UXLAB — Seoul National University (HCI group run by
        Professor Joongseek Lee). Studied at Ewha Womans University
        (Political Science & French Literature, BA; French Linguistics, MA)
        and Seoul National University (Human-Computer Interaction, PhD). :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}
      </p>
      <p>
        Academically interested in account sharing, informal coordination,
        human agency, psychological ownership, game theory, and human‑AI
        communication. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}
